    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "1 Peter",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 2,
        "summary": "Converts are newborn babes in Christ\u2014He is the chief cornerstone\u2014Saints hold a royal priesthood and are a peculiar people\u2014Saints are in subjection to the laws of man.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Wherefore laying aside all malice, and all guile, and hypocrisies, and envies, and all evil speakings,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Malice.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Guile.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Backbiting; Slander.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 101
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "As newborn babes, desire the sincere milk of the word, that ye may grow thereby:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Man, New, Spiritually Reborn.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0pure, genuine.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 3:2 (2\u20133); Heb. 5:13 (13\u201314); Mosiah 3:19.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "If so be ye have tasted that the Lord is gracious.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0experienced. Heb. 6:5 (4\u20136); Alma 36:26 (24\u201326).",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "To whom coming, as unto a living stone, disallowed indeed of men, but chosen of God, and precious,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 50:44.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye also, as lively stones, are built up a spiritual house, an holy priesthood, to offer up spiritual sacrifices, acceptable to God by Jesus Christ.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0living.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Spirituality.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Heb. 3:6.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 57
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Priesthood, Magnifying Callings within.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 100
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Types of, in Memory; Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 111
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore also it is contained in the scripture, Behold, I lay in Sion a chief corner stone, elect, precious: and he that believeth on him shall not be confounded.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Cornerstone.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 85
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 28:16.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 91
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 11:39 (37\u201340).",
                        "start": 122,
                        "end": 131
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0ashamed, disappointed.",
                        "start": 152,
                        "end": 162
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1546
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Unto you therefore which believe he is precious: but unto them which be disobedient, the stone which the builders disallowed, the same is made the head of the corner,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Disobedience.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 83
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 21:42 (42\u201346); Luke 9:22.",
                        "start": 114,
                        "end": 124
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And a stone of stumbling, and a rock of offence, even to them which stumble at the word, being disobedient: whereunto also they were appointed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 1:18 (18\u201324).",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 28:16; 2\u00a0Ne. 18:14 (13\u201315).",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Rock.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Offense.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 21:44 (33\u201346).",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 9:22 (9\u201323); 1\u00a0Thes. 5:9.",
                        "start": 133,
                        "end": 142
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But ye are a chosen generation, a royal priesthood, an holy nation, a peculiar people; that ye should shew forth the praises of him who hath called you out of darkness into his marvellous light:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Election.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Mission of Early Saints; Mission of Latter-day Saints.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Priesthood; Priesthood, Melchizedek.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 19:6. TG\u00a0Israel, Blessings of.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Nations.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0purchased, preserved; note that in Ex. 19:5 the Hebrew word is segullah, meaning \u201cspecial possession or property.\u201d TG\u00a0Israel, Mission of; Modesty; Peculiar People.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking in Darkness.",
                        "start": 159,
                        "end": 167
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Light [noun].",
                        "start": 188,
                        "end": 193
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 10
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Which in time past were not a people, but are now the people of God: which had not obtained mercy, but now have obtained mercy.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Dearly beloved, I beseech you as strangers and pilgrims, abstain from fleshly lusts, which war against the soul;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Stranger.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0resident aliens, sojourners.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Abstain.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Lust.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 83
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0War.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Having your conversation honest among the Gentiles: that, whereas they speak against you as evildoers, they may by your good works, which they shall behold, glorify God in the day of visitation.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Children of Light; Honesty.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 5:16 (14\u201316); Titus 2:8.",
                        "start": 125,
                        "end": 130
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 119
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Submit yourselves to every ordinance of man for the Lord's sake: whether it be to the king, as supreme;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Citizenship; Submissiveness.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Governments.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0superior.",
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Or unto governors, as unto them that are sent by him for the punishment of evildoers, and for the praise of them that do well.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For so is the will of God, that with well doing ye may put to silence the ignorance of foolish men:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Silence.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Ignorance.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "As free, and not using your liberty for a cloak of maliciousness, but as the servants of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Liberty.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Malice.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Servant.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Honour all men. Love the brotherhood. Fear God. Honour the king.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Respect.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Brotherhood and Sisterhood.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 24:21.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Citizenship; Kings, Earthly.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Servants, be subject to your masters with all fear; not only to the good and gentle, but also to the froward.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Col. 3:22; 1\u00a0Tim. 6:1 (1\u20132); Titus 2:9 (9\u201310).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eph. 6:5 (5\u20138).",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0crooked, wicked.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 108
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For this is thankworthy, if a man for conscience toward God endure grief, suffering wrongfully.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0pleasing, gracious.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Tribulation.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 11
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For what glory is it, if, when ye be buffeted for your faults, ye shall take it patiently? but if, when ye do well, and suffer for it, ye take it patiently, this is acceptable with God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 122:7 (7\u20138).",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 89
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forbear; Suffering.",
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 126
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 12:24. TG\u00a0Patience.",
                        "start": 146,
                        "end": 155
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0pleasing, gracious.",
                        "start": 165,
                        "end": 175
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 127,
                        "end": 134
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 162,
                        "end": 164
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For even hereunto were ye called: because Christ also suffered for us, leaving us an example, that ye should follow his steps:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Atonement through; Redemption; Self-Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 62
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Example; Jesus Christ, Exemplar.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Who did no sin, neither was guile found in his mouth:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 53:9. TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Guile; Sincere.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Who, when he was reviled, reviled not again; when he suffered, he threatened not; but committed himself to him that judgeth righteously:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 53:3 (3\u20136). TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Trials of; Retribution; Reviling.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Commitment.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Who his own self bare our sins in his own body on the tree, that we, being dead to sins, should live unto righteousness: by whose stripes ye were healed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Accountability; Self-Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Atonement through; Jesus Christ, Redeemer.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 53:5.",
                        "start": 130,
                        "end": 137
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For ye were as sheep going astray; but are now returned unto the Shepherd and Bishop of your souls.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sheep.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Good Shepherd; Shepherd.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Bishop.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}